      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUV THE NITELIFE (1) is building nicely having finished runner-up in two of her three Menangle outings since a long stint on the sidelines. Led and boxed on when beaten 3.4 metres last week so has the speed to take full advantage of the ace draw. Race fit now and looks very well placed. FOR ALWAYS ARDEN NZ (3) showed improvement for second at his most recent outing, beaten 2 metre at Newcastle. Starts from a couple of spots wider but is still drawn low enough to push forward and should be hitting his peak now. DUTY OF CARE (4) scored a win here two back then recorded a respectable second from the back row at his most recent appearance. Go well. MAC THUNDER (2) led and fought well to go under by a head as runner-up here a week ago. Draws low again and goes well at this longer distance, recording a win and a placing in two attempts.",
